events.name: Brooklyn Nets at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant loves being part of New York's basketball rivalry, even finds it funny when he hears from the opposing fans.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant leads big rally at MSG as Nets storm past Knicks

headlines.description: — When Trae Young hit a hot scoring stretch in the third period, the Washington Wizards knew they were in trouble.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young's 30 points help Hawks pull away from Wizards, 118-103

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown scored 25 points, Al Horford added 17 on 7-of-7 shooting and the Boston Celtics routed the Chicago Bulls 117-94 on Wednesday night for their 50th victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics rout Bulls for 50th, close in on No. 2 spot in East

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Bojan Bogdanovic scored 27 points, Rudy Gobert added 20 points and 10 rebounds and the Utah Jazz beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 137-101 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz rout Thunder 137-101 for 5th straight home win

headlines.description: — The Los Angeles Clippers got way too comfortable against the NBA-leading Phoenix Suns and it nearly cost them.
headlines.shortLinkText: Powell returns, Clippers beat Suns for 3rd straight win
